description:
In lichen_peer_remove(), the LOG_INF statement at line 432 attempts to log the eui64 AFTER secure_zero() has zeroed it at line 430-431:

```c
secure_zero(entry->pubkey, sizeof(entry->pubkey));
secure_zero(entry->eui64, sizeof(entry->eui64));
entry->active = false;
LOG_INF("Peer removed: %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x",
    eui64[0], eui64[1], eui64[2], eui64[3],
    eui64[4], eui64[5], eui64[6], eui64[7]);
```

The log will show the INPUT eui64 parameter (which is correct), not entry->eui64 (which would show zeros). This is actually NOT a bug - the LOG_INF uses the function parameter 'eui64' not 'entry->eui64'. On closer inspection, this is fine.

Actually, reviewing again - the code logs 'eui64' (the parameter) not 'entry->eui64' (the cleared field), so this is correct behavior. Canceling this finding.
